            <p>31 Sev 30<lb/>
                Sep 14&#47;85<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>I enclose &#36;4<lb/> on behalf of Mr &#91;&#63;&#93; Phillips<lb/> &#40;your expenses&#41; and have<lb/> no doubt a vote of thanks<lb/> will be forwarded for your<lb/> earnest effort.<lb/></p>
            <p>I hope you suffer<lb/> no inconvenience of fatigue<lb/> from fasting or your duties of<lb/> the three preceding days&#44;<lb/> and I wish for strength for<lb/> the great day Coming&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>I thank you for<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>your lines concerning the<lb/> Montefiore service and its<lb/> rendition all in English.<lb/> As you say&#44; the complexion of the<lb/> Congregation must be studied.<lb/> But I repeat&#44; I did not know<lb/> that it was you who drew up the<lb/> programme&#45;or I would have<lb/> thought &#34;twice&#34;¬ù before altering it.<lb/></p>
            <p>With regards<lb/>
                Yours &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/>
                H Pereira Mendes<lb/></p>
            <p>Did your son get his umbrella<lb/> back&#63;<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
